  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nCurrently when a custom RPC node is set historical data can't be fetched and that makes wallet's history unusable. Also in case if a new tx is sent we don't watch for confirmation.\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen. Please include designs if possible.)\nWe should give a user an option to keep using our own infura RPC for historical transfers or (if that's a privacy concern for the user) to use a custom RPC only for recent history and for watching new transfers. \n\n#### Actual behavior\n\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened. Please include screenshots if possible.)\nAs history can't be fetched (unless the user provides an archival node, which is unlikely) and error is shown and new transactions are not watched properly.",
